OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1774865180
OL,3,CMan jailed for attacking woman in
OL,4,Cassault witnessed by Barron Trump
OL,6,FRumiantsev, who lived in Canary Wharf,
OL,7,Feast London, was convicted at trial of
OL,8,Fthe assault and perverting the course
OL,9,Fof justice, relating to a letter he
OL,10,Fsent from prison attempting to
OL,11,Fpersuade the woman to drop her
OL,12,Fallegations.
OL,14,FThe jury acquitted him of two charges
OL,15,Fof rape, assault, and intentional
OL,16,Fstrangulation.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G6/14
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,409,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F408A1774865180
OL,3,CMan jailed for attacking woman in
OL,4,Cassault witnessed by Barron Trump
OL,6,FIn a victim impact statement, the
OL,7,Fwoman who was assaulted said she
OL,8,F"withdrew from the world entirely" in
OL,9,Fthe aftermath, and said she felt
OL,10,F"humiliated, afraid and ashamed".
OL,12,FShe added she is living with "constant
OL,13,Fterror and uncertainty about the
OL,14,Fdefendant's release".
OL,16,FMr Trump was a key witness in the
OL,17,Fcase, and sent an email to police last
OL,18,FMay describing the "very brief" sight
OL,19,Fhe had of the assault as it unfolded.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@bO]rD@AOUrD@`O]tD@^OUvD@TO]zD@
OL,26,ATOUzD@_O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/14
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
